message.raw:
Fixed bugs in gated clock implementation. Haven't tested gated-clocks, but a single fast and slow clock now produces almost identical output (that is the string 'fast clock' is no longer in the h5 file and it is replaced with 'flag x' where x is the first fast clock flag specified.

This means the current changes are backwards compatible (actually haven't tested WAITS, but that shouldn't have changed. Will test soon anyway)

Now begins the testing of the new gated-clocks functionality
